==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: out-of-date
<hw>out-of-date</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>same as
<er>old-fashioned</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> antique, demode, old-fashioned, old-hat(predicate),
outmoded, out of fashion(predicate), out of style(predicate), passe,
passee.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unacceptable because it is inferior to current
standards, procedures, or technology; outmoded{2}; noncurrent.</def>
<ant>current</ant>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> obsolete, outmoded{2}, superannuated.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>no longer valid.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> back(prenominal), outdated.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>out-of-door</ent>⟦br⟧
